<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These Rules are determined pursuant to Article 59 of the Environmental Agents Control Act (herein referred to as " this Act").]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Recorded data of environmental agents manufactured, processed, exported, imported, sold, and used taken each month pursuant to Article 24, Paragraph 1, of this Act shall be completed prior to the 10th day of the following month.
'When necessary', as referred to in Article 24, Paragraph 2 of this Act, means a response to one of the following circumstances.
Ⅰ.When a major epidemic occurs domestically
Ⅱ.Incidents of environmental agent pollution
Ⅲ.Incidents involving environmental agent consumer protection
Ⅳ.Training and management of national environmental agents control personnel
Ⅴ.Incidents involving social and public safety and environmental agents.
Ⅵ.Circumstances requiring a response to reports on public sentiment on domestic environmental agents
Ⅶ.Circumstances in which the competent authority carries out control, checking, or ban of environmental agents]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Article 3 'Placement', as referred to in Article 26 of this Act, means the act of placement so as to display with the intent to sell or use.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These enforcement rules shall take effect on November 10, 2006.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
